[{"from": "human", "value": "Can you provide an example of using CSS to modify a button's appearance in LimeSurvey?"}, {"from": "gpt", "value": "Certainly! To modify the appearance of a button in LimeSurvey using CSS, you would typically add rules to your theme's stylesheet. For example:
```css
/* Change the appearance of the submit button */
.btn-submit {
    background-color: #5cb85c; /* green background */
    color: white; /* white text color */
    border: none; /* remove border */
    padding: 10px 15px; /* add some padding */
    font-size: 16px; /* larger font */
    cursor: pointer; /* pointer cursor on hover */
}

.btn-submit:hover {
    background-color: #4cae4c; /* darker green on hover */
}
```
In this CSS snippet, the .btn-submit class is used to style the button, adjusting various properties such as color, size, and hover effects, ensuring an enhanced visual experience for users when interacting with the survey."}]
